T2	p 79 173	Interceptions of citrus from third countries with pests have increased by 23% up to September.
T3	p 174 478	The data is once again scandalous and highlights the latent risk of a lethal pest entering citrus fruits in the European Union. Interceptions of citrus from third countries with pests have increased by 23% up to September in relation to last year, according to information gathered by LA UNIÓ Llauradora.
T4	b 174 300	The data is once again scandalous and highlights the latent risk of a lethal pest entering citrus fruits in the European Union
T5	p 479 878	The Mercosur countries (Brazil, Argentina and Uruguay) account for 60% of all interceptions in the first nine months of the year. Brazil exceeds the 10 accumulated in 2021 at this time at 63 of this (+530%), Argentina from 5 to 8 (+200%) and Uruguay 4 for none of last year. We could also add another associated Mercosur State such as Colombia with 3 interceptions this year compared to 1 last year.
